  <brief_title>Levosimendan Pretreatment for Weaning Patients From Cardio-Pulmonary Bypass</brief_title>
  <official_title>Impact of Levosimendan Pretreatment on Weaning From Cardiopulmonary Bypass (CPB) in Patients With Diminished Left Ventricular Function Before Coronary Artery Bypass Grafting (CABG)</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Orion Corporation, Orion Pharma</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Orion Corporation, Orion Pharma</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study evaluates the efficacy of intravenous levosimendan treatment started during a
      coronary artery bypass operation to wean patients from a heart lung machine.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Levosimendan or placebo infusion is started at the time of induction of anesthesia.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
